JOHANNESBURG - A Gupta-owned coal company is being sued for allegedly failing to pay the R4.2-million needed to complete a state-of-the-art clinic in Mpumalanga.The clinic has been standing empty for months.The legal battle has been devastating for residents of the Kwazomokuhle informal settlement, near Hendrina,They said lives have been lost because there is no emergency care in the area.Is this clinic a tragic symbol of the human cost of alleged state capture? Or does the Gupta-owned Optimum Coal have a real basis for not paying?Karyn Maughan reports in the video above. eNCA